tle thing and always brought something back for my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did he look after you when your mother was out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. She never went out when he was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Yes. I did. I was the one that used to clean the knives and forks and the shoes and little jobs like that. I was the eldest and so I did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did you do these regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now how long did you continue to do these tasks? Was it up to the time you left school or did you continue to do it after you left school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Up 'til the time when I left school and then I used to do the ironing of an evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 That was after you left school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 After I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 But you didn't do the silver or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just the ironing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what about your sister, did she have any tasks she had to carry out regularly for your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well little jobs - nothing exciting. No she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. She was the baby of the family and always considered so. I was the eldest and any jobs that had to be done I had to do them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did the older children help the younger ones with things they found dif
ficult, for instance, did you help your younger sister in her dressing or eating or look after her in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I might have helped her to dress but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not to help her in eating at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did the younger child, your younger sister, help you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. No. I don't ever remember Lulu helping me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now where were you expected, sorry, there's a misprint here. Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your school days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. We'd come 
home from school and we'd have our tea and perhaps go for a walk with my mother and then come home, you see, we were always so alone, you see my father was away all the time, you see, and we'd go for a walk and come home and we were regularly in bed, all 
of us, my mother and all at a certain time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Right. Now did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Your mother or yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 It was from about ten onwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. My sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did you share the bed or the bedroom? Was it a double bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And you were the only two in that bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about the sleeping arrangements of the family? Your parents for instance, did they have their own room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My mother had her own bedroom and when my father came home he shared it with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Fine. Now what room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In the bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And how often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Oh well, that was a regular routine. Our hair was washed every Friday night, brushed and combed, and then bathed. Every Friday night of our lives, that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And when did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes. The next day, after the bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 After the bath - this was always after the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Always after the bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes we'd have a change of underthings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In the middle of the week as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And on the day after the bath on the Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Fine. Now where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Always in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Always in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Very, very rare. Perhaps if
 anybody came we'd have a cup of tea in the sitting room, but we always had our meal in the kitchen, which was a lovely kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Nice and roomy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh lovely kitchen. My mother was terribly clean, and the fireplace and everything was beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Lovely old fashioned fireplaces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now, talking of fireplaces, where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In the scullery? This wasn't the kitchen, this was the scullery beyond the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 The scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And how did she cook? What cooking equipment did she use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 The gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now when was breakfast eaten, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh breakfast before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What time would that be about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh that would be at least quarter past or half past eight. We had to be at school at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 So that would follow, about that time you would be having breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You didn't have too far to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what members of the family were present at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just my mother and two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And if your father was home would he have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well, he might have gone out a little earlier, and my mother would get up and see to him. But that was the routine though of our house.
 My mother and two sisters had the breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
So when I say to you when your father didn't have breakfast with you but went out earlier, your mother got up and got him his meal first, was that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what did you usually eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh well, we had porridge, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Summer and winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, nearly every morning of our lives. My sister wasn't fond of it but my mother used to make her eat it. And then bread an
d butter and jam or marmalade. Sometimes a boiled egg. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about Sundays, was there a different breakfast for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well that was always special, as I say, a boiled egg. We did without the porridge on a Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You didn't have bacon or anything like that, mostly boiled egg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Mostly boiled egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about midday meals? What did you have to eat and drink? A few examples you could give me for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes. We came home at half past twelve, or w
hatever time it was, and well we'd have soup, and probably a little bit of something in the oven to roast, anything such as little chops, you know a piece of chops, my mother would cook.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what vegetables and things would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Cabbage, mostly cabbage, and boiled potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Anything else you might have had? That you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 A rice pudding of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 That was a firm favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes that was a favourite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What other kinds of puddings did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 An apple steamed pudding and, you know, dumplings, things like that. But the routine was rice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Right. Now what about Sundays? Midday meal on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes that was always roast meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 It was always roast meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Roast meat, and roast potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about fish during the week? For a midday meal? Did you have fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now we always had it at tea time. Fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You always had it at tea time? I'm going to ask you about that. Now evening meals? Can you give me some examples of your evening meals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Yes fish, mostly fish. Sometimes my mother would cook a bit of ham and an egg in the evening, but it was mostly fish, because we were, she was, brought up you may say in the fishing parts and she would cook fried herrings, and boiled }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8263329\charrsid4722724 haddock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 , and things like that. That's what we had in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Can you think of anything else. Any other kind of fish you might have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well, what d'you call it, plaice. Fried. We didn't call them plaice the little ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, I remember, they're on the bone aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes on the bone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I can't remember what they're called.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did she make her own jam? Or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 She made some jam but didn't bottle any fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did she make any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Any wine or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did they buy any such as tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Nothing dried in those days you know. Everything that we had was fresh. Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Oh it was very rare we had tinned fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 It was an occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes. It was an occasion, because everything was so fresh and had to be fresh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about tinned vegetables, was this an occasion too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. Never. I can never remember my mother opening a tin of anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Really. But you can remember an occasion of her opening a tin of fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. But very occasionally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did they keep any livestock for the family, for instance, hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And how many times a week did you eat meat, could you remember roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I should say four times a week, say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh, you mean boiled ham, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I don't really think so because you'd buy that ready cooked, not in a tin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Can you think of any other kind of tinned meat that you might have eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. Nothing. Oh no. My mother wouldn't have anything in the house like that. Oh no. She was a real }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8263329\charrsid4722724 Scottish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 She liked the fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did you ever get some extra meat, such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And do you remember ever seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No we all lived very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about your father, did he have more at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well when he came home we might have something a little extra but nothing to speak of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 But would your father have more than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well my mother would see that he got a little more than the others, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now were you allowed to talk during meals? Or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Well not a lot if my mother and father were speaking, we weren't allowed to but in those days. One look from my mother would put us in our place because of course she was the one in the house, as my father was away such a lot, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No, you could choose. You could choose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You could choose what you would like to have off the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Mmm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what was your parents' attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh, nothing. We never got shouted at or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now if there was something on the tabl
e you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you, or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. You could ask to have the salt. Please pass the salt. Oh yes all that was in order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 That reminds me of Oliver Twist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. We were. Very decidedly so. My mother was the strictest woman on earth. We had to sit 
up to the table and use a knife and fork properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And when could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 "Please mother can I leave the table."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did you have to wait until everyone had finished or could you ask before?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes if you wanted to go out, you see, to play or anything. "Please mother can I leave the table?" Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And this would be permitted, fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 That's of course when your father was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did you always have the same place at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now how was the meal served? And by whom? When I say how was it served, was it put into dishes or was it served straigh
t from the saucepan on to the plates and brought in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Put on to the plates and brought in to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 From the saucepan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 From the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 From the scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Where it was served out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And who served this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Your mother. Now what order were you served in? Who was served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well when my father was at home he was served first. And then the youngest little girl and so it went on. And my mother last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And your mother last. Now where did the young
er children sit before they could feed themselves? I mean possibly you could think of what your sister did then you would know what had happened to you. Where did they sit? Before they could feed themselves, did they sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh mostly, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In what sort of chairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Because my mother used to have cushions that she used to put the little one on, and I can remember her tying him there to the back of the chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes to stop him falling out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And who fed you when you were tiny like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Your mother. Did you ever feed your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No I can't ever remember feeding her at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Was your mother an easy person to talk to, Mrs. Price.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh quite easy, yes. Quite easy to talk to. But very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 But apart from that you found her...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Oh yes, you could come in and tell her anything, or if you'd heard any little gossip you'd come in and different things like that. But a most strict woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, oh yes, she was very fond of us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now if you had any worries would you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Oh yes, you could come in and tell her anything. Anything at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. He was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did he show affection towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes he was a lovely, lovely, man. He really was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And if you had any worries could you share them with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You could talk to him about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now how did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well. Oh, I think we were all expected to be, you know, as nice as possible, and that. I was the cheeky one of the family I sup
pose. I always got the name of being the cheeky one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 But that's all you feel you can say about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 It's very difficult to imagine what your parents felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, but my sister was very quiet. My younger sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You
 see the one that died, she was quiet too. But I was always the one that if there was any trouble in the house, any little rows with us, I was the one that got the blame for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I always used to feel that, I was the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did you parents bring you up to behave towards your sisters in certain ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh we were all very happy and friendly together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did you feel your parents brought you up to feel in any particular way towards your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No just the ordinary. Just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did they say you should hit back? Or not. If another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Oh no, we got into trouble if there way anything like that. We would be brought in if there was any trouble with another child. We would be brought in the house and that was it. Finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Right. Now what kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Well I don't know. Just nice, as we were brought up, and as we saw all our relations. I suppose they thought we would all grow up the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Well we hadn't to be rude. We hadn't to back answer or anything like that. They brought us up. My mother brought us up like that. As I say, one look from her and it 
would put us in our place. But my father was quite different you see when he was home. He was all friendly and...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not seeing you so often made a fuss of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What did they think of swearing in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh well I don't think there was much of that done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You don't remember them swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No, not to any extent. No swearing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And when grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And if you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Well, we wouldn't get a beating or anything if we did something that we shouldn't have done. We wouldn't get a beating or anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. You were never punished like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. We would get scolded but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now, who would scold you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. No. He was very easy with us. Very easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well how often would you say your mother scolded you? Did she have occasion to scold you often or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh well, if I did anything, as I say I was the hero of the family, but, um, she'd scold me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh I don't remember ever getting punished, I remember back-answering my mother once 
and her coming after me with the, I don't know whether it was the brush handle or what, and I flew upstairs, and that was it. Never got anything after. That was for back-answering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Do you remember how you felt about this incident afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, I was quite pleased with myself, for running away from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Now would you say you received the ideas that you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes well my mother played the most important part in our lives. She really did. She played the most important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You feel she had the most influence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, she did, there was no doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now would you have felt that would have been the case if your father had been there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh no, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You feel this was because your father was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 That she was the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, she was father and mother you see, in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Now when you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, we'd have a little tea-party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did you receive presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And you had guests and people in to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Little girls in to tea. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day? Remember this was when you were very young.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Yes. I don't remember my father only being home one Christmas when we all hung up our stockings. We got a lovely lot of things in them. I can always remember that
. New gloves and new pennies, and apples and oranges, and all that sort of thing, because of course he wasn't home very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about the rest of the day though, when you hung up your stockings and he had the day with you, the rest of the day. Can
 you remember anything about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Yes we would all go out, the lot of us, we'd go out for a walk, and come back and have a lovely tea and that's all. And we had a piano and we could have a friend in and we'd have a good evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I was just going to ask you that. Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 So you had a piano, did you have anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just a piano. And who played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh well. I drummed a little bit on it, but we always had a friend that came...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Who could play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Who could play it and we'd all have a sing song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And when I asked you was there anyone in the family who sang, would you say there was any particular one in the family who sang very well?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You sang quite a lot, you enjoyed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And the others joined in too, of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Oh yes. Because of course all the songs were Scottish. Annie Laurie and The Bonnie Banks of Loch }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8263329\charrsid4722724 Lomond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 , and all that sort of thing. And of course my father used to love to hear me singing these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 So you really did this quite often did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 How many times would you say this happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh nearly every time he came home we'd have some kind of an evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. Snakes and Ladders and all the rest of those funny games, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Can you remember any other games at all you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No just those kind of games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 That sort of thing, Ludo and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well not particularly. My father bought some of those encyclopaedia things, but no, no particular books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You don't remember people reading a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, we had newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Newspapers; and any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well yes, I think my mother would buy a magazine when she went out. But we always had the daily papers and the evening papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about comics for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No comics weren't the order of the day at all then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 They just weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Or they were there but you didn't buy them, or they weren't even thought of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh they weren't. My mother wouldn't ha
ve those in the house. You see the sort of things that they were, what you would call 'Titbits' and all things like that she wouldn't have those things in the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 So when I ask you, do you remember your mother or father reading, what would you answer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just the newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did they ever read aloud to you when they did occasionally read, or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. Well perhaps my father would say to my mother "Listen to this.." and he'd read something out to her,
 but nothing in particular that would interest us kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My sister when she was ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now is this quite vivid in your memory is it? Or little bits of it are...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Well just a little bit of it. I don't remember the funeral itself, but I remember her dying. Because she died of diphtheria and I can remember that morning quite well. Of course we were in the other room a
nd my mother had Jessie the sister in her bed in the front room. And I can remember the lady next door being in with my mother that night and then I heard them go downstairs and shut the bedroom door. And I got out of bed and I went down and my mother was
 crying and I said, "Is Jessie dead?" and she was. And then I remember my father coming home two days after that and him broken hearted over the child. And she was so like him. She was the image of him. And that's all I remember about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 So you don't remember the day of the funeral at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. I don't remember a thing about the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Do you remember any other funeral a little later on that you might have had something to do with, of the family or a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No I don't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Do you remember ever seeing mourning clothes being worn? At a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. No. Not while we were children. Not until I grew up and my own father died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about that? Can you remember that? What year did your father die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 1910. Well tell me about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well I was twenty then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Who attended his funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My mother and myself and my sister and my two cousins and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just those numbers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes because there was nobody else in England, that would go to the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about morning clothes for that funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
Well I remember my mother being in a little black hat and a sort of velvet cape round her, but I was only in a little sort of check coat and my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not a black one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did your mother wear a veil with her hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No veil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No because we didn't have them, you see, we didn't have any, and m
y mother didn't make a lot of friends because whenever my father would say "Well pack up and I'll take you up to Scotland", because she was a very lonely person you see, and after my sister died we went away and we went to school in Scotland. We were ther
e for two or three years up there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 So she didn't really have any particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No she didn't have any particular friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about neighbours, did you ever go out visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well as I say, this neighbour next door th
at used to come in and if, she was a neighbour, as I say, and a good neighbour, if you weren't well she would come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now were you taken shopping by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, we used to go shopping. Never with my father, except when I told you he took us out in the evening when he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 But it was mainly with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 It was always with my mother, we went on the shopping expeditions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And when I ask you did you ever go out with just your father, you said to me before occasionally he did take you out when he was home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes my sisters and myself he always used to take us out and buy us something. Always brought something back for my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now do you remember any other outings with your parents? Bank Holidays for instance? Anything you might have done on an occasion like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
No. Just the Sunday School picnics. You know go away in a wagon to Raby Mere or Chester or somewhere like that. That's the only sort of outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well I'll ask you a little bit more about that in a moment because we've a question further on about Sunday School outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes. We were always away for the holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 A regular holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Six weeks in this place in Loch Vine where my father's...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 This was every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Every year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And you went for six weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Six weeks. The whole time the holidays were on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now which members of the family went? I presume if your father had been home he would have gone with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. He would take us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 He would take us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 He would take us. Yes, my mother and my sister and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Fins. And this was to Scotland? Always to the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Always to the same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what was the name again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 A place called Minnit in Argyllshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 In Argyllshire. And was this a seaside or a country place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No a seaside and country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what did you do when you went there on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh we just absolutely ran about wil
d. Go down to the shore and, you know, bathe and put our feet in the water and lie on the beach and go out in the small boats, and the fishing boats and oh it was lovely, and then go up the hills to the farms and have a ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did you sort of join in the farm activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, to help with the hay making. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about anything else you can think of that you might have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. Because of course at our holiday time it would be the time when the shooting was on, you know, t
he pheasant shooting there and they'd all pass the house going up the hill to the... oh it was really lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 It sounds wonderful. Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just the same as any other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Were they, absolutely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh absolutely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Nothing different, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Nothing any different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Sunday was the quietest day on earth. We weren't allowed to do anything. Everything was done on Saturday and there wasn't a dish washed 
on Sunday. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8263329\charrsid4722724 We got up in the morning and we had, as I said, we had prayers in the morning, every one of us knelt down by the chairs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And we got our breakfast which was, as I said, boiled egg again, and no porridge, and jam. And then at eleven o'clock go to the morning service}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
 come home and the dinner was already cooked the day before, except for a few potatoes being put on. We'd have that and then go back to the Sunday School in the afternoon and then come back again, we weren't allowed out that day at 
all, not to play or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No games or anything? No games allowed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes they never allowed us to do anything like that on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And I presume you wore different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Sunday, oh yes. Best clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Tell me about your Sunday clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You had your best clothes on of course, because you ran wild all the week and then you were all dressed up on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did your parents attend a place of worship or not? You mentioned you went to Church in the morning, did your parents go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 My mother used to come with us to Church in the morning, and my Auntie, when we were staying with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And what about your father when he was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well you see my father never went to Church to my knowledge at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what denomination was the Church that you and your mother went to on a Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Church of Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Church of Scotland. And this was a regular thing every Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. A regular thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And the Sunday School was a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 A regular thing, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now when I say did you go to Sunday School or not, of course you told me that you did go and that this was a regular thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now were there any Sunday School outings? Now this is what we were talking about before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 There was the picnic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Tell me about it. How many outings were there for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well, only once a year. Once a year and we went in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8263329\charrsid4722724 wagonette}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 . And we either went to Chester or to Raby Mere, that was when we were here in England. In Scotland you didn't have anything like that. Well that was just once a year, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did they provide the picnic for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, just buns and lemonade, and cakes and oranges and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now what other social activities organized by the Church did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Just perhaps a concert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did you belong to the choir? Did you join the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
No. But we'd have concerts, little soirees as they called them in those days. A little party and so many of you would sing and you'd have a little quartet and all that sort of things. But there wasn't the jollifications that there are these days at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Were there many of these soirees as you called them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Not many of them, no. Oh no, say three at the most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did the Church that you belonged to run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No I don't remember that, I don't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I don't. I don't remember any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did you belong to any other club organized by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 By my mother and when we were in Scotland by my Aunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Oh yes, every night. Always we had to bend down at the side of the bed and say our prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And you told me before that you had morning prayers, so when I ask you did you have family prayers, this would be altogether would it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes. It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724  morning prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You would all pray together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Do you know what his views were at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well I do know that he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724  and he voted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724  when he had to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 This was the party that he liked to see govern the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 And did he talk about, you know, any rights for the working man, did he have any strong feelings..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Did he have any strong feelings about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 
No. When you think it was sixty years ago since he died that those sort of things you know, they weren't like they are now at all. They weren't really. The men were very contented in their jobs, very contented. You never heard any of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8263329\charrsid4722724 cuffuffle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724  that there is now. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now why do you think your father held these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724  views, have you any ideas about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 I wouldn't know at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Do you happen to know what his parents were before him, whether they were the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No. I really don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 What about your mother, did she take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well she would just vote the same as my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 She had the same feelings about them as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now do you remember your father or mother voting in a General Election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Before 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Now there were several General Elections, there was one in 1900, 1906, 1910, and 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Well I remember when Lord Lever put up for parliament and he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 
Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 . I remember them voting for him. And that's all I do remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Right. Now when I asked you about the voting, do you remember this General Election when you were saying Lord Lever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 Yes, I remember Lord Lever putting up for parliament and he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11865824\charrsid4722724 Liberal
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724  and I remember my father and mother voting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 You don't remember what year that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10778156 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 No I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid471261 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10254032\charrsid4722724 But you remember them both going?
\par 
